# Next.js Architecture Standards

## Stack
- Next.js App Router + TypeScript strict mode
- Tailwind CSS v4 (no v3 syntax)
- Server Components by default; `"use client"` only for forms, animations, or state

## File Organization

```
app/
├── layout.tsx                    # fonts, root metadata
├── page.tsx                      # homepage
├── (pages)/layout.tsx            # shared Header/Footer wrapper
├── (pages)/[route]/page.tsx
├── sitemap.ts                    # dynamic sitemap
├── robots.ts
└── api/forms/submit/route.ts

components/
├── [feature-name]/               # grouped by feature
└── ui/                           # shared primitives

lib/
├── data/                         # all content (site-config.ts, navigation.ts, pages/, content/)
├── types/                        # TypeScript interfaces
└── seo/                          # metadata helpers (jsonld.ts)
```

## Page Rules

Every page MUST:
1. Import data from `lib/data/` — never hardcode content in JSX
2. Export `generateMetadata()` using the page's data object
3. Pass all data to components via props (no data fetching inside components)

```tsx
// ✅ GOOD
import { homePageData } from '@/lib/data/pages/home'
export async function generateMetadata() {
  return buildMetadata(homePageData.seo)
}
export default function HomePage() {
  return <HeroSection {...homePageData.hero} />
}

// ❌ BAD — hardcoded content, missing generateMetadata
export default function HomePage() {
  return <h1>Welcome to our site</h1>
}
```

## Route Groups
Use `app/(pages)/` for all routes that share the Header/Footer layout.
